- [ ] *‚ÄúIf we both feel that there‚Äôs a general fit in our Culture and Core Values- We‚Äôll continue on to the 2nd Interview to determine more about the particular Role that you could fill and all the details on that.  Fair enough?‚Äù*

# **üöÄ Welcome to RPI\! Your Web & Application Setup Guide**

## **üéØ What We're Accomplishing Today**

Welcome to the team\! This guide will walk you through setting up all the tools you'll need to succeed at Retirement Protectors Inc. By the end of this setup, you'll have a fully configured workspace that makes your daily work smooth and efficient.

**Time needed:** About 30-45 minutes  
 **Difficulty:** Easy (we'll guide you every step of the way\!)

---

## **üåê Phase 1: Setting Up Your Chrome Profiles**

Think of Chrome profiles like having two separate desks \- one for your personal work and one for RPI team resources. Let's set both up\!

### **Your Personal Chrome Profile**

This is YOUR workspace where you'll store your individual processes and quick links.

1. **Open Chrome** and click your profile picture (top right)  
2. **Select "Add"** to create a new profile  
3. **Name it** something like "\[Your Name\] Chrome"  
4. **Sign in** with your personal Gmail account  
5. **Choose a fun avatar** \- this helps you quickly identify which profile you're in\!

### **Your RPI Chrome Profile üè¢**

This is where all the team magic happens \- shared resources, client files, and company tools.

1. **Repeat the process** above but this time:  
2. **Name it** "RPI Chrome"  
3. **Sign in** with your RPI email (yourname@retiredprotected.com)  
4. **Pick a different avatar** so you can easily tell them apart

### **üìå Pro Tip: Pin Both to Your Taskbar\!**

* Right-click each Chrome icon when they're open  
* Select "Pin to taskbar"  
* Now you can switch between profiles with one click\!

---

## **üîñ Phase 2: Building Your Command Center (Bookmarks)**

Now let's set up your bookmarks bar \- think of this as your mission control panel where everything you need is just one click away\!

### **First, Let's Show That Bookmarks Bar**

1. Click the **three dots** menu (top right)  
2. Navigate to **Bookmarks ‚Üí Show bookmarks bar**  
3. Boom\! Your command center appears below the address bar

### **Essential Bookmarks to Add**

Here are your power tools \- add these to your RPI Chrome bookmark bar:

| Bookmark | What It Does | When You'll Use It |
| ----- | ----- | ----- |
| **üìö Dash-101** | Your training bible | Daily reference for how-tos |
| **üíº Sales Team \- Processes** | Scripts & procedures | Every client interaction |
| **üìß RPI Mail** | Quick Gmail access | Throughout the day |
| **üìÅ Active Client Files** | All client documents | Working on cases |
| **üè¢ RPI Preferred Carriers** | Carrier info hub | Product research |
| **üîß Casework Components** | Templates & tools | Building cases |
| **üìä Account Data** | Client account info | Account reviews |
| **üìÑ Field Docs** | Forms & documents | Client meetings |
| **üì¶ Product Info** | Product details | Recommendations |

### **üé® Making Your Bookmarks Pretty**

Those long "Google Drive \- " prefixes? Let's clean them up:

1. **Right-click** any bookmark  
2. Select **Edit**  
3. **Delete** the "Google Drive \- " part  
4. Keep just the essential name  
5. **Drag and drop** to arrange by frequency of use

---

## **üí¨ Phase 3: Your Communication & Work Apps**

### **Slack \- Your Team Lifeline**

This is where all team communication happens. Let's get you connected\!

1. **Download Slack** from slack.com/downloads  
2. **Install and sign in** with your RPI credentials  
3. **Pin it to your taskbar** (you'll use this A LOT)

#### **üè† Your Slack Channels:**

* **\#team-rpi** \- General team communication  
* **\#external-connections** \- Partner communications  
* **\#jmd-fixes** \- "Help, something's broken\!" üîß  
* **\#jmd-ads** \- "Wouldn't it be cool if..." üí°

#### **üí° Slack Best Practices:**

* **Fixes Channel**: Include screenshots\! A picture \= 1000 words of explanation  
* **Ads Channel**: Be specific about what you want and why  
* **Format**: "Hey Jason, \[what you need\] because \[why it helps\]"

### **ProDash \- Your Client Management Powerhouse**

This is where the real work happens\!

# **How to Request an E\&O Certificate of Insurance for Individual Agents**

## **Overview**

This guide walks you through the process of requesting an Errors & Omissions (E\&O) Certificate of Insurance for individual agents through CITA Insurance Services.

## **What You'll Need**

* Policy number  
* Agent's full name and contact information  
* Certificate holder's complete details  
* Relationship of the requesting individual to the Named Insured

## **Step-by-Step Process**

### **1\. Download the Request Form**

Download the **Certificate of Insurance Request Form** from CITA Insurance Services or request it by calling (800) 280-7250.   

[https://drive.google.com/file/d/1NW51c8sSnRBof15OF91VMhYHhtZGfUyj/view?usp=drive\_link](https://drive.google.com/file/d/1NW51c8sSnRBof15OF91VMhYHhtZGfUyj/view?usp=drive_link)

### **2\. Complete Required Information**

#### **Basic Details**

* **Date of Request**: Enter today's date  
* **Policy Number**: Your E\&O policy number (e.g., IAL0152285-04)  
* **Insured Name**: The name on the policy (e.g., Millang Financial Group LLC)

#### **Requestor Information**

* **Name**: Person requesting the certificate  
* **Title**: Their role/position  
* **Email Address or Fax**: For receiving the certificate  
* **Phone Number**: Contact number

#### **Certificate Holder Details**

* **Name**: Individual agent's full name  
* **Address**: Complete mailing address  
* **Required for Specific Individual**: Check "Yes" and provide the agent's name

### **3\. Select Relationship Type**

Choose the appropriate relationship category:

* ‚òê **Owner/Partner/Principal/Employee** of the Named Insured  
* ‚òê **Independent Contractor exclusively** doing business on behalf of the Named Insured  
* ‚òê **Independent Contractor NOT exclusively** doing business on behalf of the Named Insured  
* ‚òê **Other** (provide details)

### **4\. Submit Your Request**

**Email**: pc@citainsurance.com  
 **Fax**: (714) 978-2692

### **5\. What You'll Receive**

You'll receive a Certificate of Liability Insurance showing:

Show Image

**Key Coverage Details:**

* **Coverage Type**: Errors & Omissions Liability  
* **Policy Period**: Typically annual (e.g., 9/17/2024 to 9/17/2025)  
* **Coverage Limits**: Each Wrongful Act and Aggregate limits  
* **Deductible**: Amount (e.g., $5,000)  
* **Claims Made**: Coverage basis

## **Important Notes**

‚ö†Ô∏è **Coverage Limitation**: Coverage is provided **only** for Professional Services performed for or on behalf of the Named Insured and is subject to all terms, conditions, and exclusions of the policy.

üìã **Processing**: All requests are reviewed by a CITA representative before issuance.

## **Frequently Asked Questions**

**Q: How long does it take to process a certificate request?**  
 A: Processing times vary, but most requests are handled within 1-2 business days.

**Q: Is there a fee for certificate requests?**  
 A: Contact CITA directly for information about any applicable fees.

**Q: Can I request certificates for multiple agents at once?**  
 A: Submit separate request forms for each individual agent requiring a certificate.

**Q: What if the agent is no longer with our company?**  
 A: Coverage typically only applies while the agent is performing services for or on behalf of the Named Insured. Contact CITA to discuss specific situations.

## **B2B Onboarding Pipeline / [NDA Creation Process](https://www.loom.com/share/5aa1994fd7fb448493db9be5e194eca9?sid=8d49992f-0479-4aea-b300-b9be8f80e09f)**

### **The Acquisition Process Flow:**

**MARKETING** ‚Üí **PROSPECTING** ‚Üí **SALES** ‚Üí **INITIAL MEETING** ‚Üí **CASE ANALYSIS**

From the transcript, here's what I understand about the NDA workflow:

### **1\. NDA Process for Acquisitions:**

* When RPI is acquiring a business or book of business, they sign an NDA that essentially says **"Don't screw me \- you're opening the hood here, and I'll sue if you misuse this information"**  
* This gives RPI access to:  
  * Revenue and expense statements  
  * Tax returns (last 3 years)  
  * Detailed account information  
  * Client/carrier data

### **2\. Key Steps in Your NDA Process:**

**Step 1: Order the NDA**

* Navigate to RPI Chrome (as mentioned in your transcript)  
* Find the NDA template/form  
* Click on the NDA to begin the process

**Step 2: Edit and Customize**

* Change answers to reflect today's date  
* Update the NDA with specific acquisition details  
* Ensure all parties are properly identified

**Step 3: Document Processing**

* Convert to PDF format  
* One file type \- download as PDF directly from the system  
* Send to the appropriate person/entity being acquired

### **3\. Why NDAs Are Critical for RPI:**

From Josh's perspective in the conversations, NDAs allow RPI to:

* **Evaluate acquisition targets** by examining their books of business  
* **Run data analysis** on potential acquisitions using their proprietary calculators  
* **Assess market value adjustments (MVAs)** and surrender charges  
* **Determine which accounts could be immediately moved/improved**  
* **Calculate acquisition valuations** with high certainty

### **4\. The Acquisition Evaluation Process:**

Once the NDA is signed, RPI can:

* Import account data into their analysis tools  
* Run calculations on surrender values, market adjustments, and potential improvements  
* Identify accounts that are underperforming (like those with sub-3% returns)  
* Target accounts for immediate improvement opportunities  
* Make informed acquisition offers based on data-driven projections

This NDA process is fundamental to RPI's **Practice Acquisition Model** and supports their $1.2B growth vision by enabling them to make strategic, data-informed acquisition decisions.
